727892f-a.title: Queens: Rockaway Beach Boule - Beach 94th Street
727892f-a.text:
Rockaway Beach Boulevard, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of Beach 94th Street, showing at the corner the 281st police precinct. This building was erected in 1880 and was used as a school house from 1891 to 1901 when the new school house was opened on the other side of
the Boulevard.
October 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
